snippet: Attacks in central and northern Iraq killed at least 57 people, extending the deadliest eruption of violence to hit the country in years.
abstract: Wave of car bombings rock central and northern Iraq, killing at least 57 people and extending the deadliest eruption of violence to hit the country in years.
